Variables:-
       Variables are containers used to store data values during the execution of a program.

Types of variables:-
1.Local Variables:-
      Declared inside method or block.
      Must be initialized before use.

public void show(){
    int age=25;
    System.out.println(age);
}

2.Instance Variables:-
      Declared inside class,but outside a method.When object is created.

class Student{
    String name;
    int age;
    public void show(){
        System.out.println(name+"is"+age+"years old.");
    }
}

3.Static Variables:-
      Declared eith the static keyword.Shared among all objects of the class.

class Student{
    static String school="ABC school";
}

Rules:-
1.Must start with letter (A-Z,a-z),$ or _.
2.Subsequent characters can be letters,digits,$ or _.
3.Cannot use reserved keywords like int,class,static.
4.Variables name are case sensitive.

Datatypes:-
Syntax:-
dataType VariableName;//declaration
dataType VariableName=value;//initialisation

Primitive Datatype:-
int number=10;
double price=99.99;
char grade='A';
boolean isPassed=true;
String name="Durga Prasad";
long l=999999L;
float f=5.5f;
byte b=100;

Non-primitive:-
String name="Java";
int[] arr={1,2,3};
Student s=new Student();
Runnable r=new Task();
